job title data scientist
location portland or
reports to statistical research management
job function
the data scientist is part of the statistical operations and data science team that provides internal service to building and maintaining the data science methodology comprising comscores projection system for national television local television ondemand and digital viewership in a cross-platform measurement service this position is expected to have a particularly significant role in comscores measurement of linear television in this role the data scientist will work closely with other member of the statistical operations and data science team to work with large amount of tune-level linear television data to build algorithm tool and custom projection solution for precise cross-platform measurement using large-scale data set in a fast-paced business environment the data scientist will investigate and diagnose potential internally- and externally-facing issue and design technology improvement to the projection system to improve the way that support comscore leading cross-platform measurement product this position will require working across other functional team to meet the internal and external demand of the business
essential duties and responsibilities
independently identify appropriate data science technique and projection methodology that will be used to support comscores cross-platform measurement product and answer technical and business question
build algorithm tool custom solution and new technology from diverse and large-scale data set to enhance comscores measurement product or contribute to new product
maintain existing algorithm tool solution and methodology contributing to comscores existing measurement product
build custom solution to meet internal and client need for cross-platform measurement
work closely with other functional team including software engineering product management data operations client accounts managers and sales teams to develop and maintain the methodology contributing to comscores cross-platform measurement service
apply critical thinking to analyze process and data anomaly field client inquiry and diagnose problem and data issue these task will include working with software engineers product managers account managers sales managers and data operations analysts
summarize and visualize conclusion from large-scale data set to support the decision making of internal business stakeholder using sas excel and other tool
communicate finding and result into measure of business impact
evaluate and confirm the integrity of large source data set
be responsible for quality control and documentation of analysis and modeling to ensure on-time and accurate projection deliverable
manipulate analyze and validate large data set using sas and sql analytical software and extract quantitative and qualitative finding from large data set
creatively solve tactical and strategic problem bringing new approach to management
ownership of routine task ensuring all step are completed within expected project deadline with little supervision
qualifications
requires a ba bs in statistics mathematics or related field masters or phd degree preferred
2-4 year of relevant data science experience comscore or other medium measurement experience can be included
experience in building data science methodology and custom data solution for quantitative data measurement
general familiarity with medium industry and practice theatrical television home entertainment advertising cross-platform etc existing background in medium television or cross-platform measurement service preferred
experience in data analysis and problem solving with large amount of data strong knowledge of sas and sql programming preferred
strong excel skill
strong oral and written communication skill including the ability to communicate finding to stakeholder and document project step in detail
ability to work individually a well a partner with small and large team of other data scientists during all stage of project including planning and execution
ability to independently complete multiple simultaneous project task with little supervision
